<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-162] @OrderBy on @OneToMany does not allow ordering by @Id value</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-162</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using the following annotation:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   @OneToMany(mappedBy=&quot;root&quot;, fetch=FetchType.LAZY)&lt;br/&gt;
    @OrderBy(&quot;objectId ASC&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
    private List&amp;lt;Message&amp;gt; messages;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I get the exception &quot;Cannot order &quot;net.spatula.tally_ho.model.MessageRoot.messages&quot; on &quot;objectId&quot;, because that field is not in the default fetch group.  You can only order on fields that will be selected when the related object is loaded.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I should certainly hope that the primary key of the related object is going to be selected when the object is loaded:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    @Id&lt;br/&gt;
    @Column(name = &quot;object_id&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
    private long objectId;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Using PostgreSQL 8.1 as the database</environment>
        <key id="12364095">OPENJPA-162</key>
